# CodeRabbit Local Workflow

CodeRabbit CLI is already installed and authenticated in the terminal.

When the user asks to review code, check code quality, find bugs, or fix CodeRabbit issues:
- Run `coderabbit --agent -t uncommitted` in the current repository
- If the user wants human-readable output, run `coderabbit --plain -t uncommitted`
- Do not try to install CodeRabbit again
- Do not run CodeRabbit from the home directory; run it from the active git repository
- Do not run CodeRabbit more than 3 times for the same set of changes unless the user asks

If the request is specifically about unresolved PR comments:
- Prefer the CodeRabbit autofix workflow
- Use GitHub CLI only if it is installed and authenticated
